threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message:
having this 820-2850 board, fan spins but check no CPUVOCORE.
traced down and found PP1V05_S0 is missing

think CPU vcore won't come out if PP1V05_S0 missing.

checked on U7600, pin 13 14 =5v, pin3(en)=3v

all look good, but no output PP1V05_S0, then replaced u7600 and Q7630 Q7635
but no change.

any advice?

thanks

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: Check R1305/06 and traces to U7600.

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message:
R1305=0 oh R1306=0 oh ( schematics says 10,but i checked on another working board,they are all 0 too)
traces to resistors connected to U7600 are all good

and idea?

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: No idea. Badly soldered U7600 or bad CPU, the CPU is supplying the feedback in this circuit.

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message:
already replaced U7600 ,so.. only thing left is the CPU?
ever try to reball this model with success?

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: And what makes you thing U7600 replacement was successful? Replacing CPU is a waste of time.

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: it was pretty easy to replace... and i replaced twice U7600 already

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: Not much left then besides a dead CPU. Check the coil and cap just to be sure, but they never fail.

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message:
No Title

IT IS THE CPU.  hate doing it, but no other way around when I have to get the job done.
pull the CPU from another bad board, reballed and soldered on , spent almost an hour on it then it works now. testing it.

threads.title: A1286 820-2850 missing PP1V05_S0
threads.message: thanks again man, appreciate the hint
